bc-duplicate (1.0.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * perf(discovery): switch walk_parallel to raw syscall(SYS_getdents64).
    On warm cache /var/benchmarks, this cuts the discovery-only phase
    from 0.384 s to 0.345 s (−10%) and the --include='*.c' scenario
    from 1.375 s to 1.072 s (−22%). The 64-byte worker_slot padding
    experimented for bc-hash was evaluated here and regressed +7% on
    this workload, so it was not applied. Correctness: every file in
    every sampled duplicate group still shares the same sha256sum.
  * refactor: consume libbc-io 1.1.0 dirent_reader and libbc-runtime
    1.1.0 error_collector; drop internal duplicates.
  * Build-Depends: libbc-io-dev >= 1.1.0, libbc-runtime-dev >= 1.1.0,
    libbc-allocators-dev >= 1.1.0.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

bc-duplicate (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Parallel duplicate-file finder using a size -> partial-hash ->
    full-hash pipeline.
  * Hash algorithms: xxh3 (default), xxh128, SHA-256.
  * Subcommands: 'scan' (group output) and 'summary' (statistics).
  * Skips hardlinks (dedup by dev/ino), hidden files, symlinks, and
    pseudo-filesystems by default.
  * Adaptive single-thread / multi-thread dispatch based on
    auto-measured hardware throughput.
  * Batched I/O via io_uring when available; synchronous fallback.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
